First Lady Melania Trump attended the Family Online Safety Institute's (FOSI) 2018 annual conference, where she delivered opening remarks on the importance of responsible online behavior. She has been actively involved in promoting online safety and responsibility for children, meeting with leaders and experts in the technology and innovation fields over the past year. Mrs. Trump recently visited with 15 students from Microsoft's Council for Digital Good. At the conference, she held an on-stage discussion with four students who have been championing civil digital behavior for the next generation. The First Lady expressed her gratitude to FOSI for hosting the conference and commended the students for their positive and innovative ideas, stating that she believes they will make a real impact in promoting digital responsibility for future generations.